text: Oddrun Helene Hokland (née Lange; 29 November 1942 – 18 March 2022) was a Norwegian athlete. She competed in long jump and pentathlon at the 1964 Summer Olympics in Tokyo. She finished 16th in both events. She was born in Nesset, Reichskommissariat Norwegen (present day Norway).
